Delisting of DPRK as "sponsor of terrorism" demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 28 (KCNA) -- The south headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon) and the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) reportedly lashed out at the U.S. for terming the DPRK a "sponsor of terrorism".
 The south headquarters of Pomminryon in a statement issued on May 23 dismissed the U.S. groundless labelling as a grave move to chill the desire of the Korean nation for reunification and an unpardonable act to unleash another war on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is the biggest terrorist in the world and if the U.S. tries to ignite a new war on the Korean Peninsula in violation of the June 15 joint declaration, all the Koreans will unite as one to counter its moves, it added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south headquarters of Pomchonghakryon in a statement issued that day noted that the Bush administration's attitude of labelling the DPRK as a "sponsor of terrorism" proves that the u.s. is mapping out a plan to mount a nuclear attack on the north behind the scene of "dialogue" and demanded the withdrawal of this label.

Friendly gathering with Lao delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 28 (KCNA) -- A friendly gathering of officials of the c.c., Korean Democratic Women's Union (KDWU) and members of the delegation of the Lao Women's Union took place here yesterday.
 Present there were Pak Sun Hui, chairwoman of the central committee of the KDWU, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the delegation of the Lao Women's Union led by one Chanh Thammavong, president of its central committee, were present on invitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants talked with each other about the activities of the two women's unions and their successes and experience made in the past period, deepening the feelings of friendship.

Support to Korean people's bid for reunification called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, May 28 (KCNA) -- A meeting of solidarity with the Korean people was held in New Delhi on May 20 under the co-sponsorship of the Asian Regional Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, the All India Indo-Korean Friendship Association and the Indian Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification.
 Addressing the meeting, the secretary general of the All India Indo-Korean Friendship Association fully supported the just proposals of the DPRK for the reunification of the country and strongly demanded the immediate withdrawal of the U.S. troops and nuclear weapons from South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal to the world peace-loving people and a resolution on Korea were adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal expressed full support to the DPRK proposal to replace the Korean armistice agreement with a peace agreement and strongly demanded the U.S. pull its troops and nuclear and other mass destruction weapons out of South Korea at once and stop the joint military exercises with South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also demanded the U.S. drop down its anachronistic hostile policy towards the DPRK and show its sincerity in resuming negotiations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called upon all the peace-loving people of the world to take an active part in the international signature campaign and other movements for fully supporting the Korean people in their efforts to implement the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and achieve durable peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution said that the U.S. should give up its anachronistic ambition, withdraw its aggression forces and nuclear weapons from South Korea at once and actually create an atmosphere favorable to the reunification of Korea. It extended absolute support to the Korean people in their just struggle to build a reunified prosperous Korea.

Child miraculously cured of serious burns 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 28 (KCNA) -- A five-year-old child who had got 3rd degree burns on 78 per cent of his body was miraculously recovered at the Thongchon county people's hospital in Kangwon Province of the DPRK.
 His recovery was considered to be quite impossible from a medical point of view as his temperature was 40 degrees, pulse registered 160, breathing 70 and had most serious circulation depauperate, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the medical staff of the hospital held an emergency consultation and took urgent measures to save him under any circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People in the county visited the hospital and volunteered to donate blood, skin, bone and all other things necessary for his recovery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over ten rounds of skin grafting operations took place amid the deep concern of its population. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 1,400 people donated their blood and skin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 About 6,000 square centimeters of skin were transplanted on his body. And he received two liters of blood and a lot of sap. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was thus completely recovered in two months. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a clear reminder of the true picture of the DPRK where all the people have become a great harmonious family.
